Macro Insight: Powell HoldsBut the Pressure Is Mounting

This week, the Federal Reserve opted to hold rates steady despite growing evidence of stagflation riskPersonal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) inflation ticking up to 3.0% while GDP growth slows to just 1.4%. The decision sparked backlash, most notably from President Trump, who publicly slammed Jerome Powell for being too late and costing the country billions.

Trumps X post, while politically charged, echoes a real frustration shared by markets: Europe has cut rates ten times, while the U.S. stands stilldespite low short-term inflation prints and rising fiscal burdens.

But deeper forces are complicating this narrative:

  • Geopolitical tensions, particularly between Israel and Iran, and threats to the Strait of Hormuz (which handles ~25% of global oil shipments) could send crude prices toward $150/barrel, reigniting energy-driven inflation and cornering the Fed into a hawkish stance.

  • Fiscal dominance is tightening the Feds flexibility. As https://x.com/LynAldenContact explains in her most recent newsletter https://www.lynalden.com/june-2025-newsletter/, the U.S. deficit story is more like a train slowly overheating than a rocket heading for collision. With rising interest expenses on U.S. debt, Powell faces a lose-lose scenario: cut too soon and risk inflation, hold too long and choke growth.

Bottom line: The Fed is trapped between political pressure and global instability. Rate cuts are being demanded politically, but global supply and debt realities say otherwise. For investors, this means stay defensive, and prepare for volatility dressed in policy noise.

Crypto Market Conditions

The crypto market is undergoing a sharp pullback, and the data is offering clear insight into both the cause and the path forward. Starting with the Short-Term Holder SOPR indicator, the reading remains consistently below 1.0 a sign that recent buyers are selling at a loss. Historically, prolonged periods below this threshold indicate a market phase shifting from distribution to accumulation. If we see another wave of capitulation in the coming days, it could mark the emergence of a short-term bottom, setting the stage for a relief rebound.

Source: https://charts.checkonchain.com/btconchain/realised/sthsopr_indicator/sthsopr_indicator_dark.html

Moving to the Bitcoin Liquidation Map, we observe that a large cluster of long positions was liquidated in the 101K103K range. This event helped flush out excessive leverage and cleared unstable positioning. Now, as price continues to decline, were seeing a sharp buildup in cumulative short positioning above current price levels. If price reverses higher, these shorts could become fuel for a short squeeze, as stop-losses and forced buybacks accelerate upward momentum.

Source: https://www.coinglass.com/pro/futures/LiquidationMap

Lastly, the Sortino Ratio chart, which measures risk-adjusted returns by penalizing only downside volatility, paints a cautious picture. Since June 6th, all major assets including BTC, ETH, SOL, and even Gold have seen their Sortino ratios deteriorate into neutral or negative territory. This suggests poor compensation for risk across the board, reinforcing a risk-off environment where capital preservation takes precedence.

Altcoin Signal Layer Update - UNI Divergence Stands Out

The 30-day correlation heatmap between major altcoins and Bitcoin dominance highlights a meaningful shift in market structure. Most altcoins have remained tightly coupled with BTC trends over the past month, clustering around a neutral (orange) correlation zone. However, UNI has started to display notable divergence, transitioning into a strong positive decoupling zone (yellow-green) in the most recent week.

This upward divergence implies that UNI is behaving increasingly independently from Bitcoin, a rare characteristic in a market dominated by macro beta. In our framework, such sustained positive correlation divergence signals early formation of relative strength.

Market Thesis

The crypto market enters the new week under clear pressure, with short-term signals skewed toward further downside. Geopolitical tensions have now added an urgent layer of volatility. On June 21, the U.S. military launched a strike on Irans nuclear facilities using Tomahawk missiles and stealth bombers, significantly escalating the situation. Iran has threatened retaliation, and any disruption to the Strait of Hormuzthrough which nearly 25% of the worlds oil passescould trigger a global energy shock. Further compounding this fragile backdrop is the collapse in Sortino Ratios across all tracked assets since early June, signaling deteriorating risk-adjusted returns. Such developments may destabilize inflation expectations and potentially force the Federal Reserve to maintain higher interest rates, contrary to market hopes for easing. As real yields rise in anticipation, the crypto market could face additional tightening pressure.

Conclusion Looking Ahead

Heading into next week, the market remains delicately poised between volatility and opportunity. Price action around the $98K$101K range is criticalholding that zone may trigger a short squeeze and stabilize sentiment. But if support fails, further downside becomes likely. With no current asset providing safe harbor, and geopolitical risk escalating, traders should prioritize defensive positioning and capital preservation. We remain on high alert for sudden narrative shifts driven by macro or military developments, which could serve as either tailwinds or traps depending on positioning and timing.
